{{Infobox language |name=Gowlan |states=[[India]] |region= [[Maharashtra]], [[Madhya Pradesh]], northern [[Karnataka]] |ethnicity=[[Gowari|Gowlan people]] |speakers=20,200 |date=2000 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Indo-European |fam2=[[Indo-Iranian languages|Indo-Iranian]] |fam3=[[Indo-Aryan languages|Indo-Aryan]] |fam4=Southern |lc1=goj|ld1=Gowlan |glotto3=gowl1242 |glottoname3=Gowlan }}
'''Gowlan''' is an [[Indo-Aryan languages|Indo-Aryan]] language of India spoken by the [[Gowari|Gowlan]] people, a [[Scheduled Castes and Scheduled Tribes|Scheduled Caste]]. Gowlan speakers are situated in the [[Amravati district|Amravati]] district of [[Maharashtra]], the [[Hoshangabad district|Hoshangabad]] district of [[Madhya Pradesh]] and northern [[Karnataka]]. According to Ethnologue, Gowlan belongs to the [[Southern zone Indo-Aryan languages|Southern Zone]], and possesses substantial lexical similarities with [[Bhalay_tongue|Bhalay]].
