The '''Macedonian Wikipedia''' ({{lang-mk|{{#property:P1448}}}}) is the [[Macedonian language|Macedonian-language]] edition of [[Wikipedia]], a free and publicly editable online [[encyclopedia]].

==Overview==
This edition was started in September 2003 and has more than 92,100 articles, 224 active users, 15 administrators and 4 bureaucrats as of January 3, 2018.<ref>{{cite web| url=https://mk.wikipedia.org/wiki/%D0%A1%D0%BF%D0%B5%D1%86%D0%B8%D1%98%D0%B0%D0%BB%D0%BD%D0%B0:%D0%A1%D1%82%D0%B0%D1%82%D0%B8%D1%81%D1%82%D0%B8%D0%BA%D0%B8?uselang=en| title=Statistics| author=Macedonian Wikipedia|accessdate=2018-01-03}}</ref> It passed the 10,000 article mark in 2007.<ref>[http://www.novamakedonija.com.mk/DesktopDefault.aspx?tabindex=1&tabid=1&EditionID=773&ArticleID=37757 Nova Makedonija]{{dead link|date=January 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> The Macedonian Wikipedia has been featured in some Macedonian newspapers, such as ''[[Nova Makedonija]]'' while the project itself has been featured in a number of domestic [[news agencies]].

